  }, "HOW DID YOU FIRST HEAR ABOUT YUGABYTEDB?"), mdx("h4", {
    "id": "what-caught-your-attention-why-was-it-interesting-were-you-trying-to-solve-a-problem"
  }, "WHAT CAUGHT YOUR ATTENTION? WHY WAS IT INTERESTING? WERE YOU TRYING TO SOLVE A PROBLEM?"), mdx("p", null, "At Klarrio, we have been following YugabyteDB for over two years. Recently, we were on a hunt for a PostgreSQL-compatible database (optionally distributed), and we have decided to evaluate YugabyteDB. What caught our attention was the fact that YugabyteDB reuses the actual PostgreSQL engine but augments it with a purpose-built distributed consensus layer, which does all-things-sharding almost no-op for the operator. Our use case is a multi-tenant database with workload isolation. The choice of YugabyteDB was cemented by the ability to pin the selected tablespaces to selected cluster nodes using geo-replication features."), mdx("h2", {
    "id": "what-has-your-experience-been-like-with-yugabytedb"
  }, "WHAT HAS YOUR EXPERIENCE BEEN LIKE WITH YUGABYTEDB?"), mdx("h4", {
    "id": "what-were-your-expectations-what-have-you-been-focusing-on-what-are-your-thoughts-about-it"
  }, "WHAT WERE YOUR EXPECTATIONS? WHAT HAVE YOU BEEN FOCUSING ON? WHAT ARE YOUR THOUGHTS ABOUT IT?"), mdx("p", null, "Considering how difficult distributed systems can be and that RDBMS are not easy to automate at scale, I expected that trying out YugabyteDB would be frustrating. There are so many technologies out there never delivering on the promises they make."), mdx("p", null, "The task of evaluating different distributed database options landed on my plate. I had a specific end-to-end scenario to trial. It was surprising how painless it was to get YugabyteDB going. The core of the use case was implemented in a couple of days. YugabyteDB hasn\u2019t failed me even once in the process. What was my thought afterward? \u201CWell, that was easier than I ever expected\u201D."), mdx("h2", {
    "id": "describe-what-surprised-you-the-most"
  }, "DESCRIBE WHAT SURPRISED YOU THE MOST"), mdx("h4", {
    "id": "technically-operationally-etc"
  }, "TECHNICALLY, OPERATIONALLY, ETC."), mdx("p", null, "I had a 30+ node cluster up and running on a home lab server using Docker Compose in less than a day. It was very easy to hit the ground running. Everything else is like Postgres: databases, schemas, tablespaces on steroids, triggers, stored procedures, plugins. I really enjoy the geo-replication features."), mdx("p", null, "It\u2019s a very solid product with a permissive license. YugabyteDB is a complex distributed system but the complexity is well hidden behind an intuitive set of APIs and command line tools."), mdx("p", null, "Before jumping into the code, I spent a couple of days reading through the documentation, which was very easy to follow."), mdx("p", null, "Finally, I\u2019m not very familiar with C++ but I was able to follow the source code without major issues."), mdx("h2", {
    "id": "have-you-built-or-migrated-any-applications-to-yugabytedb"
